SEARCH

All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AppDriver
The AppDriver class is the Main class for the WordTracker application utilization.
BSTree<E>
This class is the implementation of the Binary Search Tree based on the provided BSTreeADT
BSTreeADT<E>
The BSTreeADT interface is designed to be used as a basis for the BST data structure that will be developed in the CPRG 304 class at SAIT.
BSTreeNode<E>
The class indicates the implementation of Node structure of the Binary Search Tree
InOrderIterator<E>
The implementation of an in order iterator for a binary search tree.
Iterator<E>
This interface will provide an mono-directional iterator for any of the data structures that are specified in this package.
PostOrderIterator<E>
The implementation of an post order iterator for a binary search tree.
PreOrderIterator<E>
The implementation of an pre order iterator for a binary search tree.
Word
The Word class represent the implementation of storing the information of words found as objects along with its number of appearances across files with line numbers.
WordTracker
The WordTracker class is the implementation for tracking words from the extracted text file, storing them in a Binary Search Tree as objects within each node, and tracking their appearances across files and line numbers.
